      "message": "I meant the latter, non-monotonic clock.\n\nIMHO monotonic clock support in time is not great and unreliable because it\u0027s difficult to tell if a time.Time object has a monotonic timestamp after several operations.\n\nBut in this case it\u0027s not very difficult because documentation of context.WithTimeout explicitly mentions it calls context.WithDeadline(time.Now().Add(d)), so maybe it\u0027s okay.",
